The 1977-78 [[Arkansas Razorbacks]] men's basketball team represented the [[University of Arkansas]]. The Head coach was [[Eddie Sutton]]. He would coach the Razorbacks from the 1974-75 season until the 1984-85 season<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hogstats.com/coaches/|title=HogStats.com :: Arkansas Basketball Coaches|website=www.hogstats.com|access-date=2018-11-15}}</ref>. During his tenure as head coach, the Razorbacks would end the season either first or tied for first in the Southwest Conference four times. Under Sutton the Razorbacks would be invited to the NCAA tournament a total of nine times. The most successful season of which occurred in the 1977-78 season where the team would make it all the way to the Final Four. The Razorbacks would go on to lose in the National Semifinals to the [[Kentucky Wildcats]] 64-59<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cbb/postseason/1978-ncaa.html|title=1978 NCAA Tournament Summary {{!}} College Basketball at Sports-Reference.com|website=College Basketball at Sports-Reference.com|language=en|access-date=2018-11-15}}</ref> at [[St. Louis Arena|The Checkerdome]] arena located in [[St. Louis]], [[Missouri]].
