== NCAA Tournament ==
* West ** Arkansas 73, [[Weber State University|Weber State]] 52 ** Arkansas 74, [[University of California, Los Angeles|UCLA]] 70 ** Arkansas 61, Cal St.Fullerton 58 * Final Four ** Arkansas 59, Kentucky 64 * Third Place Match ** Arkansas 71, [[Notre Dame Fighting Irish men's basketball|Notre Dame]] 69
== Notable Achievements == Eddie Sutton would leave as head coach of the University of Arkansas after the 1984-85 season with a Conference record of 139-35 (79.9%). At the end of the 1977-78 season Ron Brewer would be awarded with the [[Southwest Conference Men's Basketball Player of the Year|Southwest Conference Men's Basketball Player of the Year award]]. He would go on to be selected with the 7th overall pick by the [[Portland Trail Blazers|Portland Trailblazers]] in the [[1978 NBA draft|1978 NBA Draft]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/draft2002/history/history_78draft.html|title=NBA.com: 1978 NBA Draft, First Round|website=www.nba.com|access-date=2018-11-15}}</ref>. Sidney Moncrief would get drafted the following year by the [[Milwaukee Bucks]] and experience a successful career. He Became a five time NBA All-Star and was awarded a spot on the All-NBA First Team in 1983. His number 4 jersey was retired by the Bucks<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.upi.com/Archives/1990/01/17/The-Milwaukee-Bucks-retired-Sidney-Moncriefs-jersey-Tuesday-night/4395632552400/|title=The Milwaukee Bucks retired Sidney Moncrief's jersey Tuesday night...|work=UPI|access-date=2018-11-15|language=en}}</ref>.
