'''Sharon Speedway''' is a 3/8-mile [[dirt track racing|dirt oval]] race track located in [[Hartford Township, Trumbull County, Ohio|Hartford Township]] and named for the nearby city of [[Sharon, Pennsylvania]]. It opened in 1929, making it one of the oldest continuously running dirt ovals in the United States.<ref name="na-sharon">{{cite web|url=http://www.na-motorsports.com/Tracks/OH/Sharon.html#HistoricalNote|title=Dirt Tracks – Sharon Speedway|date=October 19, 2005|publisher=na-motorsports.com|accessdate=2009-03-10}}</ref> The track is currently part-owned and operated by the Blaney family, which includes [[NASCAR]] driver [[Dave Blaney]].  Blaney's father, and former driver, [[Lou Blaney]] originally assisted in the operation of the track.  Lou Blaney died on January 25, 2009.<ref name="Lou Blaney Dies">{{cite web|url=http://www.sharonspeedway.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=189&Itemid=1|title=The Passing Of A Racing Legend|last=Spaid|first=Brian|publisher=Sharon Speedway|accessdate=2009-03-10}}</ref>

The track currently hosts several major touring series including the [[World of Outlaws Late Model Series]] and even hosted a [[Sprint Cup Series|NASCAR Grand National]] race in 1954.  It was a 200-lap event in which Lee Petty held off Buck Baker and Herb Thomas for the win. Rusty Wallace, Tom Sneva, Tony Stewart, Lee Petty and Dave Blaney are among divers who have competed at the racetrack.<ref name="sharon-history">{{cite web|url=http://www.sharonspeedway.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=38&Itemid=48|title=History: The Dirt Way Back|publisher=Sharon Speedway|accessdate=2009-03-10}}</ref>

== Current Season ==
Sharon Speedway announced a changes in its racing format for the 2009 racing season.  The track will host sprint cars and modified stock cars on an alternating bi-weekly basis.  Promoter Dave Blaney announced that starting in the 2009 season, that Larry Mattingly will fill the position of General Manager at the Trumbull County motorsports facility.<ref name="Mattingly GM">{{cite web|url=http://www.whowon.com/Results.asp?TrackID=898&StoryID=265364|title=Mattingly Appointed Sharon Speedway General Manager|date=February 19, 2009|publisher=whowon.com|accessdate=2009-03-10|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928221900/http://www.whowon.com/Results.asp?TrackID=898&StoryID=265364|archivedate=September 28, 2011|df=}}</ref>

