{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Steetley Company Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Shireoaks]], [[Nottinghamshire]] | establishment = | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1961 | club1 = [[Nottinghamshire County Cricket Club|Nottinghamshire]] | date = 31 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/734.html Ground profile }}
'''Steetley Company Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Shireoaks]], [[Nottinghamshire]], [[England]]. The ground was laid out in 1951<ref>Cricket Grounds of Nottinghamshire P Wynne Thomas ACS 1984 p.27</ref> and the first important match on the ground was in 1955, when the [[Nottinghamshire County Cricket Club|Nottinghamshire Second XI]] played the [[Yorkshire County Cricket Club|Yorkshire Second XI]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/734_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on Steetley Company Ground]</ref> The ground has played host to both Nottinghamshire Second XI and [[Derbyshire County Cricket Club|Derbyshire Second XI]] matches in the [[Second XI Championship]] and Second XI Trophy.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/734_sec.html Second XI Championship Matches played on Steetley Company Ground]</ref><ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/734_set.html Second XI Trophy Matches played on Steetley Company Ground]</ref>
In 1961, the ground hosted a [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match in the [[County Championship]] when [[Nottinghamshire County Cricket Club|Nottinghamshire]] played [[Sussex County Cricket Club|Sussex]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/734_f.html First-Class matches played on Steetley Company Ground]</ref> [[Norman Hill (cricketer)|Norman Hill]] of Nottinghamshire made 201 [[not out]], then [[Alan Oakman]] of Sussex made 229 not out, and after two [[Declaration and forfeiture|declarations]] Sussex won by nine wickets.<ref>{{cite web |title=Nottinghamshire v Sussex 1961 |url=http://static.espncricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/1960S/1961/ENG_LOCAL/CC/NOTTS_SUSSEX_CC_05-07JUL1961.html |website=Cricinfo |accessdate=5 August 2018}}</ref> The pitch and ground were excellent, but in the relatively remote location the gate takings were poor, and Nottinghamshire never played there again.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Chalke |first1=Stephen |authorlink=Stephen Chalke|title=The Way It Was: Glimpses of English cricket's past |date=2011 |publisher=Fairfield Books |location=Bath |isbn=978-0-9568511-1-6 |pages=54-55}}</ref>
The ground held a single [[Women's One Day International cricket|Women's One Day International]] in 1979 when [[England women's cricket team|England women]] played [[West Indies women's cricket team|West Indies women]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/734_wo.html Women's One-Day International Matches played on Steetley Company Ground]</ref>
