{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Ulsan Stadium | image =<!-- Deleted image removed: [[Image:Ulsan Civic Stadium.JPG|200px]] --> | location = 865 Namoe-dong, Jung-gu, [[Ulsan]], [[South Korea]] | broke_ground = 1969 | opened = 1970 | demolished = 2003 | owner = City of Ulsan | operator = City of Ulsan | surface = Natural grass | tenants = [[Ulsan Hyundai FC|Ulsan Hyundai]] (1990–2002) | seating_capacity = 23,000 | coordinates = {{coord|35.562174|129.348065|type:landmark|display=inline}} }}
'''Ulsan Civic Stadium''' was a [[multi-purpose stadium]] located in [[Ulsan]], South Korea. In 2003, the City of Ulsan demolished this stadium. They built Ulsan Sports Complex at the same place. Ulsan Sports Complex consists of the [[Ulsan Stadium]] and [[Dongchun Gymnasium]].
