{{infobox sport event |name = World Amateur Go Championship |image = |size = |caption = |date_start = March, 1979 |date_end = |competitors = 57 players (2015) |nations = 57 |prize_money = None |other = WAGC |venue = Montien Riverside Hotel (2015) |location = {{Flagicon|THA}} [[Bangkok]] (2015) |men = {{Flagicon|KOR}} Changhun Kim (2015) }}
The '''World Amateur Go Championship''' ('''WAGC''') is an [[international]] tournament for amateur [[Go (game)|Go]] players, held once a year since 1979. The organising body is the [[International Go Federation]] (IGF).
Each participating country sends one player, although in the beginning of the contest there were multiple players from the stronger Go Countries (e.g. [[China]], [[Japan]], [[South Korea]]); in 2007 there were 68 participants.
Some of the participants have gone on to become top [[Go professional]]s.
